Using BWA and Bewtie2 samtools for alignment 

#dowload the reference sequence
$ wget http://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg38/bigZips/hg38.fa.gz
$ gunzip hg38.fa.gz

#Building index
$ bwa index -a bwtsw hg38 hg38.fa
$ bowtie2-build hg38.fa hg38

#Sequence Alignment/Map format fil
$ bwa mem hg38.fa input-F.fastq input-R.fastq > output.sam

#convert the SAM file to a BAM file
$ samtools view -S -b -o output.sam > output.bam

#Sort the BAM file by chromosome and position
$ samtools sort output.bam output_sorted.bam

#Marking possible PCR duplicates
$ picard MarkDuplicates I=output_sorted.bam O=output_sorted_marked.bam M=picard_info.txt REMOVE_DUPLICATES=true AS=true

#Indexing a BAM file (output_sorted.bam.bai)
$ samtools index output_sorted.bam

$ freebayes -p 2 -f hg38.fa  output.sorted.bam > output.vcf #-p 2 : for diploid
$ vcftools --vcf output.vcf --minQ 20 --recode --recode-INFO-all --out output_filted.vcf 

#and then you can input the output-filted.vcf file to varaft software (free software) fo annotation and fitration
